results.name: Index sequence to A089840: position of A089840(n) when applied to the right hand side subtree.
comment: The comments at A123694 concerning counts of fixed points apply also here.
link: A. Karttunen, C-program for computing the initial terms of this sequence
example: When A089840(1) = A069770 (swap binary tree sides) is applied to the right subtree of a binary tree, we get A089850 = A089840(3), thus a(1)=3. When A089840(12) = A074679 is applied to the right subtree of a binary tree, we get A154121 = A089840(3655), thus a(12)=3655.
xref: a(n) < A123694(n) for all n > 0. Used to construct A153832 and A153833.
results.author: _Antti Karttunen_, Jan 07 2009
